3 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
4 INDICATED.
5 (2) “DEVELOPMENT EXCISE TAX” MEANS AN EXCISE TAX IMPOSED BY
6 A COUNTY OR MUNICIPALITY ON THE CONSTRUCTION OR IMPROVEMENT OF A
7 BUILDING.
8 (3) “DEVELOPMENT IMPACT FEE” MEANS A FEE IMPOSED BY A
9 COUNTY OR MUNICIPALITY FOR THE PURPOSE OF FINANCING ANY OF THE CAPITAL
10 COSTS OF ADDITIONAL OR EXPANDED PUBLIC WORKS, IMPROVEMENTS, AND
11 FACILITIES REQUIRED TO ACCOMMODATE NEW CONSTRUCTION OR DEVELOPMENT.
12 (4) “QUALIFYING RESIDENTIAL REAL ESTATE PROJECT” MEANS A
13 MIXED–USE DEVELOPMENT THAT:
14 (I) INCLUDES RESIDENTIAL UNITS; AND
15 (II) IS LOCATED WITHIN A TRANSIT–ORIENTED DEVELOPMENT
16 DESIGNATED UNDER § 7–101 OF THE TRANSPORTATION ARTICLE, WHERE THE
17 DEVELOPMENT IS SERVED BY A RAIL TRANSIT STATION THAT RECEIVES AT LEAST
18 HOURLY SERVICE ON AVERAGE FROM 8:00 A.M. UNTIL 6:00 P.M. MONDAY THROUGH
19 FRIDAY.
20 (B) THIS SECTION APPLIES ONLY TO:
21 (1) A COUNTY THAT:
22 (I) IS A CHARTER COUNTY THAT IMPOSES, BY LAW,
23 DEVELOPMENT IMPACT FEES, SURCHARGES, OR DEVELOPMENT EXCISE TAXES;
24 (II) IS A CODE COUNTY WITH PUBLIC LOCAL LAWS THAT
25 REQUIRE THE PAYMENT OF DEVELOPMENT IMPACT FEES, SURCHARGES, OR
26 DEVELOPMENT EXCISE TAXES; OR
27 (III) IS A COMMISSION COUNTY THAT:
28 1. HAS BEEN AUTHORIZED TO ENACT DEVELOPMENT
29 IMPACT FEES, SURCHARGES, OR DEVELOPMENT EXCISE TAXES; AND

